        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_002",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T14:30:52Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll help you set up Stripe Connect for automated payouts. This will allow you to automatically split payments and send funds directly to manufacturer accounts. Let me break this down into steps:\n\n1. Set up Stripe Connect accounts for manufacturers\n2. Create transfer logic when orders complete\n3. Handle webhooks for transfer updates\n4. Add error handling and edge cases\n\nFirst, let's create the Stripe integration module. What's your current Stripe setup?",
      "metadata": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
        "tokens": 124
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_045",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T14:45:23Z",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Should we use Stripe Connect transfers or just split payments manually ourselves?",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_046",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T14:45:35Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Definitely use Stripe Connect transfers. Here's why:\n\n**Stripe Connect (Recommended):**\n- Automated splits handled by Stripe\n- Automatic refund handling (if customer refund, manufacturer gets debited)\n- Built-in compliance and tax handling\n- No manual reconciliation needed\n- Scales easily\n\n**Manual splits:**\n- You'd need to track every payment\n- Manual refund reconciliation (nightmare)\n- Tax compliance is on you\n- Doesn't scale\n\nStripe Connect is worth the 0.25% extra fee for the automation.",
      "metadata": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
        "tokens": 156
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_167",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T16:02:18Z",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The webhook signature verification is failing with a 400 error. Here's the error:\n\nError: No signatures found matching the expected signature for payload",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_168",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T16:02:45Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a classic issue! The problem is that body-parser middleware is consuming and modifying req.body before the signature verification runs. Stripe needs the *raw* request body to verify the signature.\n\nYou need to:\n1. Disable body-parser for the webhook route\n2. Use raw body for signature verification\n\nLet me show you the fix:",
      "metadata": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
        "tokens": 98
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "msg_169",
      "timestamp": "2024-10-27T16:03:12Z",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll create a raw body middleware and update the webhook handler.",
      "metadata": {
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
        "tokens": 23
      }
    },
